Package com.googlecode.transmuter.converter.exception

Exception Summary
BindingInstantiationException Thrown when an attempt to create a new Binding instance fails, bundling the causes.
BindingInvocationException Thrown when an invoke operation fails, bundling the cause.
ConverterTypeIncompatibleWithBindingException Thrown when the given converter type is not compatible with the one extracted from the given binding.
ConverterTypeInstantiationException Thrown when an attempt to create a new ConverterType instance fails, bundling the causes.
InaccessibleMethodException Thrown when the method given to a Binding constructor cannot be externally accessed.
InvalidParameterTypeException Thrown when the parameter type of a would-be converter method is considered invalid.
InvalidReturnTypeException Thrown when the return type of a would-be converter method is considered invalid.
MethodInstanceIncompatibilityException Thrown when the given method cannot be invoked on the given instance.
MethodOwnerTypeIncompatibilityException Thrown when the given type (dubbed owner type) is not in the given method's declaring class hierarchy.
NullInstanceWithNonStaticMethodException Thrown when there is an attempt to bind a non-static method to a null instance.
WrongParameterCountException Thrown when the given method has an invalid number of parameters.
